  them the twelve leaders of the orders who divide the months; and for the three hundred
  and sixty (days) there are heads over thousands who divide the days; and for the four
  intercalary days there are the leaders which sunder <hi type="super">12</hi> the four parts of the year.  And
  these heads over thousands are intercalated between <hi type="super">13</hi> leader and leader, each behind a
